{
 "_about": "Cross-check dataset harvested from named, citable academic papers (see _sources) for the Soap Calc iodine-consistency gate and oil-data quality arc. Numbers verified by two independent blind PDF reads plus first-principles arithmetic (2026-07-19). Use as an external published-reference sanity band alongside the app profile-derived SAP/IV oracle; do NOT treat as ground truth to overwrite app values without review.",
 "_verification": "Giakoumis & Toscano tables each read twice by independent blind agents; all iodine values and equations matched. One correction applied: Giakoumis castor 1.36 belongs to palmitic (C16:0), not myristic (C14:0). profileDerivedIodineValueOilBasis computed via AOCS-basis formula IV = glycerideFactor * sum(FA% * 253.809 * nDoubleBonds / MW_FA).",
 "_sources": {
  "giakoumis2018": "Giakoumis EG (2018). Analysis of 22 vegetable oils' physico-chemical properties and fatty acid composition, Renewable Energy. DOI 10.1016/j.renene.2018.03.057. Literature-compiled statistical means (695 papers). Reports iodine value; NO saponification value.",
  "toscano2012": "Toscano G et al. (2012). Vegetable oil and fat viscosity forecast models based on iodine number and saponification number, Biomass & Bioenergy 46:511-516. DOI 10.1016/j.biombioe.2012.07.009. Lab-measured paired IV (ISO 3961) + SV (ISO 3657).",
  "warra2010": "Warra AA, Hassan LG, Gunu SY, Jega SA (2010). Cold-Process Synthesis and Properties of Soaps..., Nigerian J. Basic & Applied Science 18(2):315-321. Primary measured SAP + IV + finished-bar pH."
 },
 "_iodineConsistencyNote": "deltaProfileMinusReported (profile-derived oil-basis IV minus Giakoumis's reported IV) scatters BOTH directions across oils, roughly +/-10 to 16, because Giakoumis compiles the FA-profile column and the iodine column as independent statistical means from different literature pools. So for a single oil, treat profile-derived IV and reported IV as two independent estimates; neither is authoritative to better than ~10 IV units. A per-oil delta alone is NOT a reliable inconsistency signal. Real inconsistency requires triangulation against a third source (this file's Toscano pairs, Warra, or the app's own profile). See _anomalies.",
 "_anomalies": [
  "palm: Giakoumis reported IV 43.2 disagrees with (a) its own profile (derived ~53.5), (b) Toscano palm 47.8-52.5, and (c) standard oleochemical refs (50-55) simultaneously -> Giakoumis palm IV is the low outlier; do not adopt it. Prefer ~50-53.",
  "babassu: reported IV 21.7 vs profile-derived ~15.9 (delta -5.8); within single-source scatter, minor, but babassu here does resolve real C8 5.68 / C10 5.61 (candidate corrected profile for the app's inflated-babassu concern)."
 ],
 "_caveats": [
  "Giakoumis provides NO SAP values and does NOT cover palm-kernel, tallow, lard, shea, or cocoa butter.",
  "rapeseed (high-erucic) is distinct from canola; appId left null to avoid conflating with canola-oil.",
  "Toscano oils are of deliberately unspecified provenance/cultivar (falls under the reference-derived anonymity rule)."
 ],
